node.text:
@Modlin_Group sold this stunning residence in Soho, New York City 😍 Swipe left 👀

73 Wooster Street. 
Last Asking $14,950,000
—

Located on a quiet, treelined cobblestone street, this 4 bedroom, 3 full and one half bathroom home spans approximately 4511 square feet. The home has an authentic loft feel typified with its giant casement windows and up to 14 foot ceiling heights throughout. This residence has undergone a full renovation creating a true bespoke home experience featuring custom millwork + craftsmanship such as reclaimed French oak floors, a vintage French 18th Century fireplace mantle, coffered ceilings, a custom temperature-controlled 500+ bottle wine cellar and an automated Savant smart home system throughout.

Harmoniously blending the boutique nature of old-world Soho with the amenities expected in the new New York, 73 Wooster is one of Soho's preeminent five-star boutique buildings with only 6 large residences, a 24-hour doorman and onsite storage.  With no shortage of world-class shopping and dining, Soho’s charm also lies in its cobblestone streets, cast-iron architecture, and sweeping lofts and galleries.
